This paper deals with differential privacy, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). It also involves Kalman filtering, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on state trajectories generated by agents with linear dynamics, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also involves error and entropy bounds, which are concepts from information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper provides guidelines for privacy calibration, which could be considered a topic in data science (cs.DS).
